##DESCRIPTION
##  Find slope of secant lines of a curve, then guess the slope of
##  a tangent line
##ENDDESCRIPTION

##KEYWORDS('secant lines', 'tangent line')

DOCUMENT();        # This should be the first executable line in the problem.

loadMacros(
"PG.pl",
"PGbasicmacros.pl",
"PGchoicemacros.pl",
"PGanswermacros.pl",
"PGauxiliaryFunctions.pl"
);

TEXT(&beginproblem);
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$a1 = random(3,8,1);
$x0 = random(2,5,1);
$y0 = $x0*$x0 + $x0 + $a1;
$x1 = $x0 + 0.1;
$x01 = $x0 + 0.01;
$x9 =  $x0 - 0.1;
$x99 = $x0- 0.01;

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
The point \( P($x0 , $y0 ) \) lies on the curve
\( y = x^2 + x + $a1 \).  If \( Q \) is the point
\( (x, x^2 + x + $a1 ) \), find the slope of the secant line
\( PQ \) for the following values of \( x \).
$BR
If \( x= $x1 \), the slope of \( PQ \) is:
\{ans_rule(25) \}
$BR
EOT

$ans = $x0 +$x1 + 1;
&ANS(std_num_cmp($ans));

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
and if \( x= $x01 \), the slope of \( PQ \) is:
\{ans_rule(25) \}
$BR
EOT

$ans = $x0 +$x01 + 1;
&ANS(std_num_cmp($ans));

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
and if \( x= $x9 \), the slope of \( PQ \) is:
\{ans_rule(25) \}
$BR
EOT

$ans = $x0 +$x9 + 1;
&ANS(std_num_cmp($ans));

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
and if \( x= $x99 \), the slope of \( PQ \) is:
\{ans_rule(25) \}
$BR
EOT

$ans = $x0 +$x99 + 1;
&ANS(std_num_cmp($ans));

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
Based on the above results, guess the slope of the tangent
line to the curve at \( P($x0 , $y0 ) \).
\{ans_rule(25) \}
$BR
EOT

$ans = 2*$x0 + 1;
&ANS(std_num_cmp($ans,1));

ENDDOCUMENT();        # This should be the last executable line in the problem.

